1 (4) The department shall provide an annual report to the legislature, in accordance with 5-11-210,
2 detailing:
3 (a) each waiting list for a covered service, including the number of people on the waiting list each
4 month;
5 (b) efforts underway by the department to reduce or eliminate the waiting list; and
6 (c) the date the department expects the waiting list to be eliminated.
7 (5) For the purposes of this section, "waiting list" means a list of persons enrolled or presumptively
8 enrolled in the Montana medicaid program who are eligible for a service but cannot receive that service in 90 or
9 fewer days due to a lack of funding, available providers, enrollment slots, or other service supply issues.
10
11 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Codification instruction. [Section 1] is intended to be codified as an
12 integral part of Title 53, chapter 6, and the provisions of Title 53, chapter 6, apply to [section 1].
13 - END -
